    {
      "type": "teach",
      "title": "Putting words together",
      "body": "Shavian has no capital letters — instead, a small dot before a word marks it as a name (like ·Sam). Otherwise sentences read just like English, word by word, only spelled the way they sound. 𐑞 𐑒𐑨𐑑 𐑕𐑨𐑑 reads as \"the cat sat\"."
    },
    {
      "type": "teach",
      "title": "A few little words",
      "body": "A handful of common words get their own fixed spelling worth memorizing: I is just 𐑲 and a is 𐑩. The very commonest words shrink to a single letter: the is 𐑞, and is 𐑯, and to is 𐑑. You'll run into them constantly."
    },
